Blocks.childText: LUDWIC. 7s. J. G. DOUTHIT. 1 Hark, my soul, it is the Lord! 'Tis thy Sav-iour, hear his word! Je - sus speaks, he speaks to thee: "Say, poor sin - ner, lov'st thou me? 172 Bap., 491. Meth., 473. Pres., 42. 2 "I delivered thee when bound, Deeper than the depths beneath, And, when wounded, healed thy wound; Free and faithful, strong as death. Sought thee wand'ring, set thee right, 5 Thou shalt see my glory soon, Turned thy darkness into light. When the work of grace is done, 3 "Can a mother's tender care, Partner of my throne shalt be: Cease toward the child she bare? Say, poor sinner, lov'st thou me?" Yes, she may forgetful be, 6 Lord, it is my chief complaint Yet will I remember thee. That my love is still SO faint; 4 "Mine is an unchanging love, Yet I love thee and adore: Higher than the heights above, o for grace to love thee more? BARTIMEUS 8s & 7s. DANIEL READ, 1804. 1 Come, thou long ex- pect - ed Je- sus, Born to set thy peo - ple free; From our fears and sins re-lease us, Let us find our rest in thee: 173 Bap., 193. Meth., 934. Pres., 41. 2 Israel's Strength and Consolation, Born to reign in us for ever, Hope of all the earth thou art,- Now thy gracious kingdom bring: Dear Desire of every nation, 4 By thine own Eternal Spirit, Joy of every longing heart. Rule in all our hearts alone; 3 Born thy people to deliver; By thine all-sufficient merit, Born a child, and yet a King, Raise us to thy glorious throne. 87 Lord, I deliver thee when bound, When he sough, hear his word! LUDWIC
